    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-10T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-10T06:00:00-05:00" n="295"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-10T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 10, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 10—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Important items: <list>
                        <item>First. Japanese Consul General has asked that he be given list of
                            American property and investments outside Settlement and north and east
                            of Hongkew contiguous to Japanese sector. I am to furnish the list
                            tomorrow.</item>
                        <item>Second. It is learned on reliable authority that Japanese naval
                            authorities have applied to pilot association for 16 pilots to pilot
                            transports into Shanghai on the 12th.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation and Nanking for information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
